<subSubSection id="B73393D4623CF3886583B5FC42A9E828" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5FA0C4762BEDFA953BD3B3E61D48F803" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A09ED67B3EB02203F3A2F9A1A2CFECD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mexico (Chiapas, Colima, Jalisco, 
<normalizedToken id="812FC5B14DBD4210B504B345B7071544" originalValue="Michoacán">Michoacan</normalizedToken>
, Oaxaca, Sinaloa), Guatemala (El Progreso, Huehuetenango, Zacapa), El Salvador, Honduras, Nicaragua, and Costa Rica, in oak forest, pine forest, and tropical dry forest, in open disturbed areas, riparian areas, road edges, canyons and ravines, thickets and hedges, sometimes on limestone, 0-1300 m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AFCB76FC482C9909ECE5EC8C3D3AE18F" captionStart="Figure 97" captionStartId="F97" captionText="Figure 97. Map of geographic distribution of L. scandens var. flavicans from Mexico to Honduras based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure97" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480111" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">97</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
